HIV/AIDS: China ta ba da rahoton ƙaruwar sabbin cututtuka da kashi 14 cikin 100
Kasar Sin ta sanar da karuwar kashi 14 cikin 100 na yawan mutanen da ke fama da cutar HIV da AIDS.
Mutane fiye da 820,000 suna da waɗannan cututtuka, in ji majiyoyin kiwon lafiya.
An samu sabbin mutane kusan 40,000 a cikin kwata na biyu na 2018.
Yawancin sababbin cututtuka suna faruwa ne ta hanyar jima'i, wanda ya nuna canji daga baya.
A wasu yankuna na kasar Sin, cutar HIV ta bazu a baya sakamakon kamuwa da jini.
Amma adadin mutanen da suka kamu da cutar HIV ta wannan hanyar ya ragu zuwa kusan sifili, kamar yadda hukumomin lafiya na kasar Sin suka ce a wani taro a lardin Yunnan.
Amma duk da haka, shekara bayan shekara, adadin mutanen da ke da cutar HIV da AIDS a China ya ƙaru da dubu ɗari.
Cutar HIV ta hanyar jima'i matsala ce mai gaggawa a cikin al'ummar LGBT na kasar Sin.
An haramta luwadi a China a 1997, amma har yanzu ana nuna wa mutanen LGBT wariya.
Domin al'adun ƙasar, wasu bincike sun kimanta cewa kashi 70-90 na maza da suke yin jima'i da maza suna aurar da mata.
Yawancin yaduwar cututtuka suna faruwa ne saboda rashin kariya a lokacin jima'i a cikin jima'i.
A 2003, gwamnatin China ta yi alkawarin samar da magungunan cutar HIV ga kowa a matsayin wani ɓangare na ƙoƙarin da take yi na magance matsalar.
